President Obama announced his intent to nominate Sue K. Brown as Ambassador to the Republic of Montenegro and David L. Carden as Representative of the United States of America to the Association of Southeast Asian Nations. He also appointed Stephen E. Condrey as Chairman of the Federal Salary Council, Lou Cannon, Jeffrey David Cox, Rex L. Facer, Bill Fenaughty, Colleen Kelley, and Jacqueline Simon as members of the Federal Salary Council. These individuals bring a wealth of knowledge and experience to their new roles and President Obama is confident that they will serve the American people well.